{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17636931","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17636931"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:35:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:35:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17616"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17616","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17616"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.58,0.09,0,0.09,0.24]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10330"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79483"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10330","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10330"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17616"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64805"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6658"},{"type":"tags","id":"6664"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24163"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26012"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79483","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/79483"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe external carotid artery provides the main arterial supply to the structures of the head and face through its various branches.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the course of the superficial temporal artery?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Crosses anterior to the external auditory meatus and ascends superficially","Runs deep to the masseter muscle","Passes through the foramen spinosum","Enters the pterygomaxillary fissure","Courses along the anterior border of the masseter"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperficial temporal artery (image) crosses anterior to the external auditory meatus and ascends superficially\u003C/strong\u003E in the temporal region. It is one of the terminal branches of the external carotid artery and can be easily palpated anterior to the ear.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options describe the courses of other arteries:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERuns deep to the masseter muscle\u003C/strong\u003E - This is not the course of the superficial temporal artery, which remains superficial throughout its course\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPasses through the foramen spinosum\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the course of the middle meningeal artery, a branch of the maxillary artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnters the pterygomaxillary fissure\u003C/strong\u003E - This is part of the course of the maxillary artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECourses along the anterior border of the masseter\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes the course of the facial artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe superficial temporal artery divides into anterior and posterior branches that supply the scalp and temporal region. It is clinically significant as it can be used to palpate the temporal pulse and is vulnerable during facial trauma.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The superficial temporal artery is a terminal branch of the external carotid artery that supplies the scalp and temporal region.","The facial artery branches from the external carotid artery and supplies the face, running along the anterior border of the masseter muscle.","The maxillary artery is the largest terminal branch of the external carotid artery and supplies deep structures of the face."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u201cExternal Carotid Artery\u201d by Mikael H\u00e4ggstr\u00f6m is under\u00a0Public Domain. \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:External_carotid_artery.png\u003E","Moore KL, Dalley AF, Agur A. Clinically Oriented Anatomy. 8th ed. Lippincott Williams and Wilkins; 2017."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64805"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17616"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21380"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21380","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21380"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/g9iodkc33H5bwHn5uYh3XPsPqjMPQt.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/g9iodkc33H5bwHn5uYh3XPsPqjMPQt.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":592}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64805","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64805"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-14T20:02:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-14T20:03:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10330"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"79483"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical stud